  "prompt": "What is a recipe like Whole Foods mock chicken salad?",
  "response": "While Whole Foods doesn't publish their exact recipe, many online copycat recipes aim to recreate their popular mock chicken salad. Here's a breakdown of a general recipe, combining common ingredients and techniques found in various attempts:\n\n**Core Ingredients:**\n\n*   **Base (Texturized Vegetable Protein - TVP):** 1 cup dried TVP granules\n*   **Broth:** 1 cup vegetable broth (for rehydrating TVP)\n*   **Vegan Mayo:** 1 cup (e.g., Follow Your Heart Vegenaise, Just Mayo)\n*   **Celery:** 1/2 cup, finely diced\n*   **Red Onion:** 1/4 cup, finely diced\n*   **Fresh Dill:** 2 tablespoons, chopped\n*   **Dijon Mustard:** 1 tablespoon\n*   **Lemon Juice:** 1 tablespoon\n*   **Seasoning Blend:** 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon black pepper, 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder, 1/4 teaspoon onion powder\n*   **Optional ingredients for added flavour/ texture:**\n*   **Sweet Pickle Relish:** 1-2 tablespoons\n*   **Chopped Walnuts or Pecans:** 1/4 cup (toasted, for extra flavor)\n*   **Grated Carrot:** 1/4 cup\n*   **Apple:** 1/4 cup, finely diced (for sweetness and crunch)\n*   **Curry powder:** 1/4 teaspoon (for warmth)\n*   **Smoked paprika:** 1/4 teaspoon (for a smoky flavour)\n\n**Instructions:**\n\n1.  **Rehydrate the TVP:** In a bowl, combine the dry TVP granules with the vegetable broth. Stir well, making sure all the TVP is submerged. Let it sit for 10-15 minutes, or until the TVP has absorbed most of the liquid and is soft.\n\n2.  **Drain Excess Liquid (If Necessary):** If there's excess liquid in the TVP after rehydration, gently squeeze it out. This will prevent the salad from being soggy.\n\n3.  **Prepare the Vegetables:** While the TVP is rehydrating, finely dice the celery, red onion, and, if using, apple and carrot. Chop the fresh dill.\n\n4.  **Combine Ingredients:** In a large bowl, combine the rehydrated TVP, vegan mayo, diced celery, red onion, dill, Dijon mustard, and lemon juice.\n\n5.  **Season:** Add the salt, pepper, garlic powder, and onion powder. Mix everything together well.\n\n6.  **Add Optional Ingredients:** If using, stir in the sweet pickle relish, chopped walnuts/pecans, grated carrot, apple, curry powder or smoked paprika.\n\n7.  **Adjust Consistency & Taste:** Taste the salad and adjust the seasoning as needed. Add more vegan mayo if you prefer a creamier consistency. Add a squeeze of lemon juice or a pinch of salt/pepper to brighten/deepen the flavors.\n\n8.  **Chill:** Cover the bowl and refrigerate the mock chicken salad for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to meld. Chilling also helps the TVP firm up a bit.\n\n9.  **Serve:** Serve on bread or crackers, in lettuce wraps, or on top of a salad.\n\n**Tips for a Great Mock Chicken Salad:**\n\n*   **TVP Texture:** The key to a good mock chicken salad is rehydrating the TVP correctly. Don't over-rehydrate it, or it will be mushy. Squeezing out excess liquid is important.\n*   **Finely Diced Vegetables:** The smaller the vegetable pieces, the better they will incorporate into the salad.\n*   **High-Quality Vegan Mayo:** The vegan mayo is a crucial component of the flavor and texture. Choose a brand you enjoy.\n*   **Adjust to Taste:** This recipe is a starting point. Adjust the ingredients and seasonings to your personal preferences.\n*   **Let it Chill:** Chilling is essential for the flavors to meld and the TVP to firm up.\n*   **Add Smoke:** A tiny amount of smoked paprika can make a big difference by adding the \"chicken\" flavour.\n\n**Why These Ingredients Work:**\n\n*   **TVP:** Provides the protein and \"chicken-like\" texture.\n*   **Vegan Mayo:** Creates the creaminess and binds the ingredients together.\n*   **Celery & Onion:** Adds crunch and savory flavor.\n*   **Dill:** Provides a fresh, herby note that is classic in chicken salad.\n*   **Dijon Mustard & Lemon Juice:** Adds tanginess and balance.\n*   **Seasonings:** Enhance the overall flavor.\n*   **Optional Ingredients:**  Offer variety in flavor and texture.\n\nEnjoy your homemade mock chicken salad! Experiment with different ingredients and ratios to find your perfect version.\n",
